title: Attribute Error when importing pytorch
body_html:
I installed pytorch from source code. After installation, I tried to import pytorch, but I got the following error message: (using ipython)

In [1]: import torch
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AttributeError                            Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-1-c031d3dd82fc> in <module>()
----> 1 import torch

/home/kb539/.pyenv/versions/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/torch/__init__.pyc in <module>()
    337 import torch.multiprocessing
    338 import torch.sparse
--> 339 _C._init_names(list(torch._tensor_classes) + list(torch._storage_classes))
    340 
    341 # attach docstrings to torch and tensor functions

AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute '_init_names'

I don't know how to fix this problem.....

In [1]: import torch
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AttributeError                            Traceback (most recent call last)

```
----> 1 import torch

/home/kb539/.pyenv/versions/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/torch/__init__.pyc in <module>()
    337 import torch.multiprocessing
    338 import torch.sparse
--> 339 _C._init_names(list(torch._tensor_classes) + list(torch._storage_classes))
    340 
    341 # attach docstrings to torch and tensor functions

AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute '_init_names'
```
I don't know how to fix this problem.....
